Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{450%grams} lengthways into 1cm slices, then chop into 1cm wide
chips (no need to peel).

Pop the chips onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, season with
@salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, bake on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}.

In the meantime, place the @THIS™ Isn't Pork Sausages{6%units} on a large
baking tray in a single layer and drizzle with oil. Season with salt and
pepper.

Bake on the middle shelf of the oven until golden brown, ~{15-18%minutes}. Turn
halfway through cooking.

> IMPORTANT: Ensure they're piping hot throughout.

When the chips are halfway through cooking, turn them and sprinkle over the
@Grated Hard Italian Style Cheese{20%grams}.

While everything roasts, halve, peel and thinly slice the @onion{1}.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a #frying pan{} on medium heat.

Once hot, add the onion and season with salt and pepper. Fry, stirring
occasionally, until golden, ~{8-10%minutes}.

Add the @Balsamic Vinegar{12%ml} and @Sugar for the Onions{1%tsp} (see pantry for
amount). Cook until caramelised, ~{1-2%minutes} more.

Add the @Butter{10%grams} (see pantry for amount) to the pan until melted, then
sprinkle over the @Plain Flour{1%tbsp} (see pantry for amount). Cook, stirring
regularly, for ~{1%minute}.

Add the @Water for the Gravy{150%ml} (see pantry for amount),
@Vegetable Stock Paste{10%grams} and @Worcester Sauce{15%grams} to the pan.

Bring to the boil, then lower the heat and simmer until thickened,
~{2-3%minutes}. Add a splash of water if it's a little thick.

When there are 5 mins of cooking time remaining, bring half a #saucepan{} of
water to the boil with @salt{1/4%tsp}.

When boiling, add the @peas{120%grams} to the water and cook for
~{2-3%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #colander{} and return to the pan. Add a knob of
butter (if you have any) and season with salt and pepper.

Share your THIS™ Isn't Pork sausages between your serving plates with your
cheesy chips and peas alongside.

Spoon the onion gravy over the sausages to finish.

Enjoy!